{"id":200,"date":"2023-09-21T23:59:37","date_gmt":"2023-09-21T23:59:37","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/jwc.hubstarebs.com.au\/?page_id=200"},"modified":"2023-09-27T21:17:54","modified_gmt":"2023-09-27T11:17:54","slug":"currently-renting","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.jwc.com.au\/currently-renting\/","title":{"rendered":"Currently Renting"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">For Non-Urgent Repairs<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To request general maintenance, kindly complete the form below and provide as much detail as possible. Once approved by the rental provider, non-urgent maintenance requests will be assigned to skilled tradesmen and scheduled for the next business day. In cases where damage is determined to be the result of renter negligence or malicious damage, the renter bears the responsibility for repair costs, as outlined in the lease agreement. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As per the terms of the lease, renters are required to facilitate access to the property for tradesmen. This involves being present at the property to grant access. The tradesperson will contact the renter in advance using the provided contact number or, if necessary, utilise our office spare keys.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">For Urgent Repairs<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you encounter a situation outside of our regular office hours, including weekends, and deem it urgent requiring immediate attention for a repair, please consult the following list of tradesmen and their contact information. If you are uncertain whether the issue warrants immediate repair, we encourage you to get in touch with the respective tradesman to discuss the matter so they can assess whether immediate action is necessary.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-1 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Electricians<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Mil